article.headline: Hartford 64, New Hampshire 62
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- David Ruffin hit a baseline jumper with a minute to play and Aaron Cook made a crucial steal and hit a free throw to lead Hartford to a 64-62 win over New Hampshire Sunday. Hartford (7-10, 3-5 America East) lost a 13-point lead in the second half as the Wildcats went up 61-59 with 1:51 left to play. Charles Ford tied the game for Hartford with a pair of free throws, but New Hampshire's Ben Sturgill made a free throw to put the Wildcats back up 62-61. Ruffin hit his jumper. New Hampshire's Chris Vetrano missed a go-ahead 3-pointer and his teammate Ioannis Karalis got the rebound. But Cook stole the ball with 14.8 seconds remaining and was fouled. Vetrano missed another 3-pointer in the closing seconds. Cook finished with a game-high 25 points. Ruffin had 18 points and seven rebounds. New Hampshire (6-11, 2-6) was led by Sturgill's 18 points and 12 rebounds. Jermaine Anderson added nine points for the Wildcats.
